# 📝 Introduction

Percentage means **"per hundred"** or **"out of 100."**

It is represented using the symbol **%**.

Example

```text
50%

↓

50 out of 100

↓

50/100

↓

0.5
```

Percentages are one of the most important aptitude topics because they are used in:

- Profit & Loss
- Simple Interest
- Compound Interest
- Ratio & Proportion
- Data Interpretation
- Discounts

━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━

# 📘 Formula 1 – Find Percentage

When the value and total are given.

```text
Percentage

=

(Value ÷ Total)

×100
```

### Example

40 students passed out of 50.

```text
Percentage

=(40÷50)

×100

=80%
```

━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━

# 📘 Formula 2 – Find Value

When the percentage is given.

```text
Value

=(Percentage × Total)

÷100
```

### Example

Find 30% of 500.

```text
=(30×500)

÷100

=150
```

━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━

# 📘 Formula 3 – Percentage Increase

```text
Increase %

=

(Increase ÷ Original Value)

×100
```

Where

```text
Increase

=

New Value − Original Value
```

### Example

Salary increases from ₹20,000 to ₹25,000.

Increase

```text
25000−20000

=5000
```

Percentage Increase

```text
=(5000÷20000)

×100

=25%
```

━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━

# 📘 Formula 4 – Percentage Decrease

```text
Decrease %

=

(Decrease ÷ Original Value)

×100
```

Where

```text
Decrease

=

Original Value − New Value
```

### Example

Mobile price decreases from ₹40,000 to ₹30,000.

Decrease

```text
40000−30000

=10000
```

Percentage

```text
=(10000÷40000)

×100

=25%
```

━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━

