# ❌ Common Mistakes

### Wrong

Using the **New Value** instead of the **Increase**.

Example

```text
20000 → 25000

Wrong

25000÷20000×100
```

Correct

```text
Increase

=25000−20000

=5000

↓

5000÷20000×100

=25%
```

━━━━━━━━━━━━━━

### Wrong

Using the **New Price** instead of the **Decrease**.

Correct

```text
Decrease

=Old−New
```

━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━

# 🎯 Interview Tips

Always identify these four values first.

```text
Original Value

↓

New Value

↓

Increase / Decrease

↓

Apply Formula
```

This avoids most percentage mistakes in placement exams.

